<dl id="n58038b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n58" href="#n58038b">N58 (VI.B.30)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n58all.htm#n58038b"> 38(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> fistful of / berries of / quicken of / Dubros = / immortality <small>Green</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n58038b"><li>FW 376.28 </li><li><a href="../../flex/mg/lexmg.htm#n58038b">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/mg/l39mg.htm#n58038b">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n58038b">MS BL 47480-314v</ms> </li><li>JJA 55:541 <a name="mfd7" href="../../FF/fdra/mda.htm#mgd5">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/mg/mgd5.htm#n58038b">Draft: II.3&sect;7.5</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[THE PURSUIT OF DIARMUID AND GRAINNE]</font> <font color="green">[Diarmuid and Grainne journey northward to a forest when they make a hunting booth. Diarmuid the goes to the Searban Lochlannach, and gets from him license to hunt and to chase provided that he never meddles with the berries of the quicken tree of Dubros; berries that no sickness]</font> seizes any one that eats three of them, and they who eat feel the exhilaration of wine and the satisfying of old mead; and were it at the age of a century, <mark>he that tasteth them would return again to be thirty years old</mark>. <font color="green">[The berries are protected by Searban, a fierce giant with one eye in the centre of his forehead, who is fated]</font> not to die until there be struck upon him three strokes of the iron club that he has. <font color="green">[Finn asks as a fine from the sons of his father Cumall&apos;s enemies that they bring him]</font> the head of a warrior <font color="green">[Diarmuid]</font>, or <mark>a fistful of the berries of the quicken tree of Dubros</mark> <small> Tom Peete Cross and Clark Harris Slover, <a name="AIT2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AIT2"><cite title="source">Ancient Irish Tales</cite></a> ([Nov. 1936]) 394ff</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: see also <a name="n58039a" href="n58all.htm#n58039a">N58 (VI.B.30):039(a)</a> </mm> </dd></dl>
